{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01NUeNtiiP6EXrXvRDKT9P8H","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me carefully analyze the knowledge file against the source file to identify any issues.\n\n**V1: Omission Check**\n\nLet me go through the source file section by section:\n\n**Source intro**: \"本章では、UI標準に対する主要な修正要望に関して、以下の観点で解説している。1. 具体的に何をどのように修正すればよいか。2. 修正による影響範囲とコストはどの程度か。\" - This is an introductory navigation sentence, acceptable to omit.\n\n**UI標準1.1 - 対応する端末とブラウザ (s1)**:\n\n\nFor the browser addition request, the knowledge file captures the essential testing requirement but misses the nuance about how standard-compliant browsers generally work fine despite minor display differences—the key takeaway is that adding new browsers requires thorough testing on those devices. Looking more carefully at the source material, I notice the knowledge file is missing a specific requirement: the need to thoroughly test on the target device when adding new browser support. While the file does cover the general risks of modifying existing code, this testing prerequisite is an important best practice that's been omitted. I'm also checking the coverage for IE6/7 support questions and display mode changes, which seem adequately addressed in the knowledge file.\n\nNow examining the UI standards sections more closely, I see the table for UI標準1.2 is correctly reproduced. But for the color configuration section, the knowledge file references CSS color definitions without including the actual color values themselves—the source shows specific RGB values for base colors and accent colors that should be documented. I'm verifying the knowledge file's coverage against the source documentation. The color parameter descriptions are adequately captured even without the specific RGB values—those implementation details aren't essential for understanding what each parameter controls. For the footer section, both the source and knowledge file correctly point to modifying the nablarch-template-app_aside plugin content. UI標準2.1 looks solid, and I'm moving on to check UI標準2.2.\n\nThe knowledge file includes the style table for different display modes but skips the directory structure for nablarch-template-app_header, which is fine since that's just illustrative. UI標準2.3 through 2.6 all check out, and I notice the typo in \"nablarch-widet-button\" is preserved consistently in the hints. Now I'm looking at the section count discrepancy—the source has 19 headings but only 9 sections are documented, so I need to examine the RST structure to understand what's being missed. ヘッダ領域、サイドメニュー、フッター、共通エラーメッセージ表示など、各画面要素の表示内容を調整したいという要望が複数あるようだ。また、ワイド表示モードの切替条件や無効化、さらにワイド表示時の画面構成についても検討が必要になってきている。\n\nコンパクト表示モードやナロー表示モードでの表示内容の調整、テーブル表示での横スクロール対応、そして入出力項目の表示調整など、複数の表示モードに対応した細かい調整が必要になっている。\n\nタブキーによるフォーカス移動順番の制御、必須項目の表示形式、エラーメッセージの表示方法、ボタンの表示順序や権限に応じた表示制御といった、ユーザーインタラクションに関わる仕様も整理する必要がある。さらにブラウザ間の表示差異への対応も検討している。 I've verified each section against the source material and found no fabrications—all claims trace back to the original content, including the code examples and tables. The 9 sections in the knowledge file properly correspond to the 9 top-level headings in the source, so the section count is appropriate despite the automated warning counting all heading levels.\n\nNow I'm checking the hints for completeness across each section. The first section covers all the key device-fix variants and browser constraints like IE6/7 support limitations and missing features such as Web Font and hover pseudo-selector support. Moving through the remaining sections to verify their hint coverage is similarly thorough. Continuing through the remaining sections—s7 covers the narrow layout variant, s8 has comprehensive widget hints including button styling, and s9 addresses core CSS utilities like border-radius and drop-shadow effects with IE8 compatibility notes. The hints appear thorough across all sections, though I'm noticing s1 might have a minor gap regarding device testing requirements for browser support. Looking at the full context from the source, I see there's actually a more substantial omission here. The knowledge file doesn't capture the critical warning about the risks of modifying source code when adding browser support—specifically that direct modifications could break existing browser compatibility. This is important decision-making information that should be included. I'm noticing I missed a key prerequisite—the source emphasizes testing thoroughly on the target device before making any changes, but my summary jumped straight to the risks of modifying the source directly. I should flag this as a minor omission since the testing requirement is actually a necessary step that comes before deciding whether modifications are needed at all.\n\nNow let me recount the RST headings more carefully to understand this section count discrepancy. I'm seeing level 1 headings for the main title, then level 2 headings for each UI standard example, but the warning suggests there's a mismatch between what the knowledge file captured and the actual structure of the source document.\n\nLooking at the level 2 headings, I count 9 of them across the different UI standards. The warning about 19 source headings likely includes all the level 3 sub-headings as well, which would explain the difference. The knowledge file's 9 sections are appropriately organized around those main level 2 headings, so this shouldn't be flagged as an issue.\n\nSo my assessment comes down to one minor finding: the testing requirement mentioned in s1 before adding browser support wasn't explicitly called out, though it's a fairly standard prerequisite. The knowledge file is otherwise well-structured and comprehensive.\n\nNow I'm checking the color scheme tip from s3. The source has a detailed note about @mainColor2 being the base text color and how its contrast with @baseColor should be stronger than @mainColor1's contrast. The knowledge file captures this guidance accurately in a condensed format. The source also includes CSS code examples showing default color values and adjustment examples, but since the knowledge file already covers the parameter definitions and their roles, those specific RGB values aren't critical for implementation decisions. I'll consider this acceptable.\n\nLooking at the rest of the source, there's a figure reference for a color scheme sample image, which is appropriately left out of the knowledge file. After reviewing everything, the only minor gap I found is about browser testing. Let me prepare the final output.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":21476,"cache_read_input_tokens":18400,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":21476,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d584438c-d4a6-480c-9351-b5ff4d06621b","uuid":"7fdda878-d27f-4577-95bb-cc8e7c2336d2"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01NUeNtiiP6EXrXvRDKT9P8H","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01QV7bxpoKdGm6U5DKz9vPVo","name":"StructuredOutput","input":{"file_id":"testing-framework-ui-dev-doc-reference-ui-standard--s1","status":"has_issues","findings":[{"category":"omission","severity":"minor","location":"s1 (対応ブラウザの追加)","description":"The source explicitly states that when adding browser support, thorough testing on the target device is required ('当該の端末でのテストを十分に実施する必要がある'). The knowledge file omits this prerequisite step and also omits the conditional context that the risk of direct source modification arises specifically when problems are detected after testing ('テストの結果、修正を要する問題が検出された場合'). As a result, the knowledge file loses the logical sequence: test first → if problems found → avoid direct plugin modification → use nablarch-device-fix instead.","source_evidence":"プロジェクト側で対応ブラウザを追加する場合は、当該の端末でのテストを十分に実施する必要がある。テストの結果、修正を要する問題が検出された場合、当該のソースコード(プラグイン)を直接修正すると、既存の対応ブラウザ上の挙動に問題を生じさせる危険性がある。"}]}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":21476,"cache_read_input_tokens":18400,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":21476,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d584438c-d4a6-480c-9351-b5ff4d06621b","uuid":"2618d72e-73b5-41c2-90e7-428c56039260"}
