{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01MFCGUJBKd8LYLy721jqGJd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Summary**: The knowledge file is in good shape overall with one minor omission.\n\n**Finding**: In `s1`, the source establishes a clear sequence — (1) test thoroughly on the target device first, then (2) if problems are found, avoid direct plugin modification in favor of `nablarch-device-fix`. The knowledge file omits the prerequisite testing step and the conditional framing, presenting the plugin-modification risk as an absolute warning rather than a consequence of detected test failures. This loses the logical workflow an implementer needs.\n\n**Section count warning**: The automated warning (\"Section count 9 < source headings 19\") is not a real issue. The source has 9 level-2 RST headings (`---`) matching the 9 knowledge sections; the remaining 10 headings are level-3 sub-questions (`===`) correctly folded into each section's content."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5940,"cache_read_input_tokens":39876,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5940,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d584438c-d4a6-480c-9351-b5ff4d06621b","uuid":"3532de05-debe-4bf1-bd1c-dc3d283a20d1"}
